PRIOR ART / ATTRIBUTION
=======================

The HPACK Huffman decode automaton proven correct here descends, algorithmically,
from the nibble-DFA decode table in nghttp2:

    nghttp2 — HTTP/2 C Library
    Copyright (c) 2013 Tatsuhiro Tsujikawa
    MIT License — https://github.com/nghttp2/nghttp2

  which is in turn after:

    R. Pajarola, "Fast Prefix Code Processing," Proceedings of the International
    Conference on Information Technology: Coding and Computing (ITCC), 2003.

The shipped sources of this repository contain NO nghttp2 source code. The verified
C in `cbits/generated/` is produced by KaRaMeL from the F* proof, whose transition
table is generated from the RFC 7541 Appendix B code table and proved equal to the
specification decoder (`Hpack.Huffman.Refine.DfaTable`). nghttp2 is referenced only:

  (a) as the algorithmic origin of the nibble-DFA approach this work proves correct; and
  (b) as an optional differential-testing oracle (`test/test_diff.c`), which links the
      nghttp2 library at test time but incorporates none of its source.

The git history of `cbits/hpack_huffman.c` includes earlier revisions that embedded
nghttp2's MIT-licensed decode table directly (before the verified implementation
replaced it); those revisions remain attributed to nghttp2 (MIT) as above.
